The paper discusses machine learning black boxes and techniques for explaining them in an interpretable manner, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses biases and adversarial attacks, which are topics in cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the paper uses real-world datasets and discusses image classification, which are topics in computer vision (cs.CV).
